100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Won this race in 2024 and might have needed belated return; big player if building on that
column37: Progressive for Gemma Tutty last season, winning the 3yo Dash on Derby day and posting a personal best when beating nine rivals in this contest (just 1lb higher today) 12 months ago; weak in the market and might have needed the run after over ten months off when only sixth of eight here on reappearance; big player if building on that.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Close second at Southwell on Sunday; should be in the thick of things again off same mark
column37: Nearly as good as ever at the age of six and he won at the Shergar Cup (5f, good to firm; at least as effective on soft/heavy) in August; close second under Ethan Tindall at Southwell on Sunday and should be in the thick of things again off the same mark.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Likeable mare; up 13lb for last two wins; will need career best to complete hat-trick
column37: Likeable mare with eight wins to her name, including at Sandown (5f, soft) and Ascot (5f, good to soft) in the last four weeks; impossible to rule out but she's gone up 13lb in total for those successes and she'll need a career best to complete the hat-trick.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Down the field last three starts in hot races; has had wind op since and may bounce back
column37: Comes into the reckoning on his close second at Newcastle in May off 1lb higher, and, although down the field three times since, those runs came in hot races including the Wokingham and Stewards' Cup; needs to bounce back but he's had two months off after wind surgery and it's certainly possible.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Some way behind Vintage Clarets when well held at Southwell on Sunday; others appeal more
column37: Three 6f wins for Michael Bell; placed just once for current yard and followed that run with a poor effort at Southwell on Sunday (finished well behind Vintage Clarets); others appeal more.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column32: Ingleby Bloodstock Ltd & The Ivy League
column36: Has not made the frame in six runs this year; mark is tumbling but he's risky
column37: Capable 5f performer on his day but has not made the frame in six runs this year; a slow start meant he couldn't adopt his usual front-running tactics at York five weeks ago, and his mark is tumbling, but he's risky.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column32: D Caslin, P Wilcock & M Cantillon
column36: Went down narrowly at Doncaster 13 days ago; C&D winner in May; has plenty in his favour
column37: Back in top form again after a mid-summer lull, and he went down only narrowly at Doncaster (5f, soft; also handles good to firm) 13 days ago; was a C&D winner in May and has plenty in his favour.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Fine start for new connections when second at Chepstow but three runs since have been poor
column37: Useful as a 2yo for Karl Burke; fine start for new connections when second at Chepstow (6f, good) in August but three runs since have been underwhelming, including in a tongue-strap; cheekpieces are now applied.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Speedy type with a progressive profile; fine second at Ascot and may improve further
column37: Like most of his speedy family he's a 5f specialist, and he arrives in top form after finishing second to Woolhampton in a big field at Ascot three weeks ago; meets the winner on 4lb better terms and may not have reached his ceiling just yet; serious contender.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Snapped a long losing run at Doncaster 13 days ago and should be thereabouts again
column37: Snapped a long losing run at Doncaster (5f, soft) 13 days ago, battling on gamely after four months off; nudged back up only 2lb and should be thereabouts again.

column20: 100/30 Woolhampton, 5/1 Vintage Clarets,  Duran, 13/2 All Ways Glamorous, 15/2 Blue Storm, 10/1 I'm Next, 12/1 Lethal Nymph, 14/1 Germanic, 16/1 Queen's Guard,  Tees Spirit, 20/1 King Of Light
column36: Improving; up in class after winning at Musselburgh last time but can't be ruled out
column37: Steadily progressive sort who notched win number three at Musselburgh (5f, good to soft) two weeks ago, leading over 1f out; he's up markedly in grade from a Class 5 to a Class 2 but he's thriving and can't be ruled out.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Yet to match 2yo best this year but down in grade and still has a bit of potential
column37: Useful 2yo; satisfactory seasonal return at Newmarket in May but he hasn't fired in two starts since (gelded before latest); drops into a 0-90 and still has time to fulfil his promise after just seven starts.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Three 6f wins at Newmarket this summer; dropped right away at Newmarket on Thursday
column37: Completed a hat-trick, all at Newmarket's July course over 6f on good to firm, with her hard-fought win five weeks ago; dropped away having forced the pace at Newmarket on Thursday; needs to bounce back quickly.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Not lived up to market billing in either handicap but dropped 5lb since latest; unexposed
column37: Strong form in defeat as a 2yo; bolted up, albeit in a weak race, at Salisbury in May, but lesser efforts have followed in hot handicaps at Royal Ascot and Newmarket since; gelded during his 11-week absence and a 5lb drop in the weights helps too; dangerous mark now.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column32: John Sagar And Dunham Trading Ltd
column36: 2024 winner; fine second in Ayr Bronze Cup last week; this veteran should be in the mix
column37: Veteran who showed he retained a chunk of ability when flashing home for second in the Ayr Bronze Cup eight days ago (6f, soft); 3l clear of the others in the stands' side group on that occasion so a 3lb rise is perfectly fair; won this race 12 months ago off 1lb lower and he is high on the list, for all drying ground will suit others more.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Low-key run in Ayr Silver Cup; feasible mark on this year's best; more exposed than many
column37: Never in contention in the Ayr Silver Cup last week; mark not beyond him judged on this year's best but he has few secrets now.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Has won over 6f but best form has come at shorter; dangerous mark but others appeal more
column37: Has won over 6f but his best efforts have come over 5f; not beaten far into sixth at York three weeks ago and on a lowly mark but others appeal more at this trip.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Lightly raced 3yo; runner-up off this mark at Goodwood latest; up in class this time
column37: Won an AW novice on his second start; runner-up in two of his three completed starts in handicaps, latterly a six-runner affair at Goodwood 25 days ago (6f, heavy; tongue tied first time); needs more in this field.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: C&D winner; good 3rd here in May but struggled twice since; back to last winning mark
column37: C&D winner; back to his last winning mark and his C&D third in May (off 3lb higher) confirmed he retained ability; two defeats since leave him with more to prove.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Class 4 win at Windsor and then had a troubled run at Newmarket last week; draw a query
column37: Things clicked for him when beating 11 rivals in a Class 4 at Windsor (6f, good) 19 days ago; only seventh of ten at Newmarket last week but he was short of room for a sustained period at a crucial stage; could bounce back with a good run if stall 1 is no hindrance.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: C&D winner on a good mark; drying ground in his favour; not discounted
column37: On a handy mark and has run well in two of his four C&D runs; couldn't reward market support at Southwell this month but drying ground is in his favour and he can't be discounted.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Best effort so far with recent second at Yarmouth (6f, soft); 2lb higher in a better race
column37: Off the mark at the ninth attempt when winning a 6f maiden at Southwell last month; better form when second in a Yarmouth handicap (6f, soft) ten days ago; 2lb rise in stronger company could find him out.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Three course wins last year as well as 2nd in this race; eyecatcher latest; shortlisted
column37: Three wins here last season and also chased home Woven in this race; has been a shade disappointing since his Beverley win in April but he is now 5lb lower than for that victory and his latest Doncaster run was eyecatching; probably wouldn't want it to dry out too much but he's a leading contender.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Two wins at a lower level in May; drying conditions will help but others appeal more
column37: Prominent racer who won over 5f at Beverley and 6f at York in May; could provide the best pace amongst the low-drawn runners and he will appreciate drying conditions.

column20: 100/30 Woven, 13/2 Realign,  Wild Clary, 7/1 Vantheman, 8/1 Topwarrior, 10/1 Uncle Don,  Grant Wood,  Trilby, 12/1 Angel Shared,  Sergeant Pep, 16/1 Pals Battalion, 25/1 Ingleby Archie, 50/1 Bear Force One
column36: Three heavy defeats sandwich 40-1 surprise victory at Doncaster; drops to 6f for 1st time
column37: Prominent racer; three heavy defeats from four runs for his new stable in 2025 but the other run saw him spring a 40-1 surprise at Doncaster; blinkers join the eyeshields today but he drops to 6f for the first time on his 39th start.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: Promising for Aidan O'Brien but last in Listed race for new yard last November; off since
column37: Quickly reached a useful level for Aidan O'Brien at the end of last summer, winning a 1m Leopardstown maiden then 1l third in a Dundalk Listed race over an extended 1m2f; subsequently allowed to leave Ballydoyle for only 18,000gns and last of ten in 1m2f Newcastle Listed event for new connections last November; off since and a watching brief is very much the call after gelding and wind operations.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: Good 3yo form and fair sixth when 9-2 for Lincoln in March; off since; retains potential
column37: Wrapped up a good 3yo campaign with smart effort for second of 12 in 1m Doncaster handicap (soft) last October; couldn't justify favouritism but still made a respectable return to the track when sixth of 22 in the Lincoln there (1m, good to soft) in March; off a further six months since but evidently capable when fresh and remains with untapped potential.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column27: Exors Of The Late Mr O J Williams
column36: Not at best since the spring and others are more persuasive
column37: Made a good start to the term with creditable thirds in competitive handicaps at Thirsk and York in the spring but hasn't been in quite the same form since; his mark has edged down as a result but others are still more persuasive.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: Well held at Doncaster latest but runner-up over C&D and at Chester prior to that
column37: Record is only 1-12 but good seconds over C&D and at Chester (7.5f; cheekpieces applied) last month; raced too keenly when disappointing at the Doncaster St Leger meeting since but claims on the earlier efforts.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: Made a winning reappearance at Newbury last weekend but quick turnaround a slight worry
column37: Better than ever when landing a 7f Newbury handicap (good to soft) on last Saturday's belated reappearance; a 3lb rise is fair but a second outing in quick succession after an absence has to be a slight concern.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: 2-2 on AW, with form of latter win strongly boosted; smart prospect now switching to turf
column37: First foal of the multiple Group 1 winner Laurens; unbeaten in 7f Newcastle maiden and 1m Southwell novice seven months apart; his Southwell win has been boosted by the second, third, fourth and fifth winning since; lacks experience for a race of this nature but rates a smart prospect now switching to turf.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: Has touch of seconditis but building up solid record and should give another good account
column37: Soft-ground novice win last autumn; has a touch of seconditis over 6f/7f this term but he's built up a solid record and 1m looks worth a go; might be one who needs his mind making up and De Sousa taking the reins for the first time could also be a positive.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: Can blow the start but Glorious Goodwood win shows he's useful on day; fair fifth latest
column37: Showed he's a useful sort with Glorious Goodwood success (1m, heavy) in July; one of his slow starts scuppered him back at Goodwood next time but he got away on terms when a respectable fifth of 14 to Treble Tee at Doncaster (1m, good) a fortnight ago.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: Not disgraced in warm 3yo 7f handicaps last twice and remains unexposed back at 1m
column37: Won a pair of 7f novice events (good to firm/good) in May; not disgraced in warm 7f 3yo handicaps at Glorious Goodwood and Doncaster St Leger meeting since; shaped on Town Moor as if this return to 1m may suit; remains unexposed.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column36: Better this year than his form figures may suggest and not without hope off reduced mark
column37: Only 1-10 but running better this season than his form figures may suggest and contested a Group 2 on his penultimate run; he's not without hope off a reduced mark.

column20: 7/2 First Ambition, 4/1 Midnight Gun, 5/1 Fondo Blanco, 13/2 El Matador, 10/1 Hawksbill,  Christian David,  Tilted Kilt, 12/1 Principality,  Intrusively, 16/1 La Trinidad, 40/1 Platoon
column27: Sun Bloodstock S A R L
column36: Second in Silver Bowl over C&D in spring and another good C&D second last time
column37: 0-12 since debut win on AW but there have been some good runs since, notably his second in the Silver Bowl over C&D (good) in May; bounced straight back from a poor run on AW when runner-up over C&D on good ground again three weeks ago; ought to be in the mix.

column4: J&P Civil Engineering British EBF Maiden Stakes (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/2 Noble Journey, 4/1 Lost Boys,  Poseidon's Warrior, 9/2 Saxophonic, 15/2 Golden Knight, 8/1 Edwin Hubble, 12/1 Double Combo, 16/1 Brighton View, 20/1 Houndswood Willow, 66/1 Helios Path, 200/1 Risk Averse Rebel
column36: Dam from classy family; trainer having a good season with his 2yos; not ruled out on debut
column37: First foal; dam once-raced sister to 1m2f/1m4f Group 2 winner Beautiful Romance, out of 1m4f Group 3 winner; trainer is having a good season with his 2yos and had one win on debut here at 14-1 in June; this Palace Pier newcomer is not ruled out.

column4: J&P Civil Engineering British EBF Maiden Stakes (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/2 Noble Journey, 4/1 Lost Boys,  Poseidon's Warrior, 9/2 Saxophonic, 15/2 Golden Knight, 8/1 Edwin Hubble, 12/1 Double Combo, 16/1 Brighton View, 20/1 Houndswood Willow, 66/1 Helios Path, 200/1 Risk Averse Rebel
column36: Half-brother to two winners; trainer won this with a well-backed newcomer last year
column37: Fourth foal; Dubawi half-brother to winners Cabelleroso (7f AW; RPR 89) and Big Time Rascal (6f; 67); dam well-bred 7f/1m winner (97); trainer won this with a well-backed newcomer last year; watch the betting.

column4: J&P Civil Engineering British EBF Maiden Stakes (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/2 Noble Journey, 4/1 Lost Boys,  Poseidon's Warrior, 9/2 Saxophonic, 15/2 Golden Knight, 8/1 Edwin Hubble, 12/1 Double Combo, 16/1 Brighton View, 20/1 Houndswood Willow, 66/1 Helios Path, 200/1 Risk Averse Rebel

column4: J&P Civil Engineering British EBF Maiden Stakes (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/2 Noble Journey, 4/1 Lost Boys,  Poseidon's Warrior, 9/2 Saxophonic, 15/2 Golden Knight, 8/1 Edwin Hubble, 12/1 Double Combo, 16/1 Brighton View, 20/1 Houndswood Willow, 66/1 Helios Path, 200/1 Risk Averse Rebel
column36: 220,000euros 2yo breeze-ups; yard has healthy strike-rate with 2yos here; possible player
column37: 220,000euros 2yo breeze-ups; sixth foal; Camelot half-brother to four winners notably Delphi (1m-1m6f including Australian Group 2) and Credenza (Group-placed 8.4f 2yo; dam 5f and 6f (Group 3) 2yo winner; trainer has a healthy 20% strike-rate here with his 2yos; possible player on debut.

column4: J&P Civil Engineering British EBF Maiden Stakes (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/2 Noble Journey, 4/1 Lost Boys,  Poseidon's Warrior, 9/2 Saxophonic, 15/2 Golden Knight, 8/1 Edwin Hubble, 12/1 Double Combo, 16/1 Brighton View, 20/1 Houndswood Willow, 66/1 Helios Path, 200/1 Risk Averse Rebel
column36: 4,000gns 2yo breeze-ups; half-brother to four winners but may be best watched on debut
column37: 6,000euros yearling, resold 10,000gns yearling, 4,000gns 2yo breeze-ups; 11th foal; Coulsty half-brother to four winners including Jackamundo (7f-11.4f including 2yo; RPR 86), Ballycommon (7f 2yo; 78) and Mirzam (1m4f; 78); dam 7f/1m winner (69); he may be best watched on debut.

column4: J&P Civil Engineering British EBF Maiden Stakes (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/2 Noble Journey, 4/1 Lost Boys,  Poseidon's Warrior, 9/2 Saxophonic, 15/2 Golden Knight, 8/1 Edwin Hubble, 12/1 Double Combo, 16/1 Brighton View, 20/1 Houndswood Willow, 66/1 Helios Path, 200/1 Risk Averse Rebel
column36: Makes debut with yard in fine form; one to watch in betting but others are more compelling
column37: 50,000euros yearling; fifth foal; Starspangledbanner half-brother to 7f AW winner Souffionne (RPR 78); unraced dam from talented family; makes debut with yard in fine form and he's one to watch in the betting, but others are more compelling.

column4: J&P Civil Engineering British EBF Maiden Stakes (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/2 Noble Journey, 4/1 Lost Boys,  Poseidon's Warrior, 9/2 Saxophonic, 15/2 Golden Knight, 8/1 Edwin Hubble, 12/1 Double Combo, 16/1 Brighton View, 20/1 Houndswood Willow, 66/1 Helios Path, 200/1 Risk Averse Rebel
column36: Close third of five at Ascot on second start and form has been franked; leading claims
column37: Ran okay when third of seven on debut at Newbury (1m, good) last month and built on that with close third of five at Ascot (1m, soft) three weeks ago, form that has been franked by the runner-up; leading claims today.

column37: Revitalised by switch to new stable at end of last season, winning twice over 2m6f before close second in valuable novices' handicap at Sandown (2m4f, good; jumped left throughout); will be a tough nut to crack if still in similar form after five-month break.

column4: Never Say Die IPA Handicap Chase (GBB Race)

column37: 3-6 over fences, the latest win gained at Kempton (2m4f, soft; made all) in February; needs to return from seven-month break in prime form to have any chance off current mark but the forecast good ground won't be a problem.

column4: Never Say Die IPA Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Mahons Glory, 7/2 Time To Bite, 4/1 Champagne Gold, 5/1 El Rio, 6/1 Coastguard Station, 8/1 Jet Plane, 20/1 Frere d'Armes
column36: Did well in hunter chases last season; only fifth on recent handicap return
column37: Six-time chase winner (once here); did well in hunter chases towards end of last season, most notably when second of 29 over the big Aintree fences in April, but was just a respectable fifth when back in a handicap this month and needs that run to have brought him on.

column4: Never Say Die IPA Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Mahons Glory, 7/2 Time To Bite, 4/1 Champagne Gold, 5/1 El Rio, 6/1 Coastguard Station, 8/1 Jet Plane, 20/1 Frere d'Armes

column37: Very useful at peak for Henry de Bromhead in Ireland and came good for new stable at third attempt, causing 33-1 surprise with narrow success at Cartmel (2m5f, good) last month; it's hard to tell whether he'll be in the right mood again here but a 4lb rise ought to be manageable if he is.

column4: Never Say Die IPA Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Mahons Glory, 7/2 Time To Bite, 4/1 Champagne Gold, 5/1 El Rio, 6/1 Coastguard Station, 8/1 Jet Plane, 20/1 Frere d'Armes
column36: Won hunter chase in May but has become far too inconsistent to rely upon
column37: Back in good nick when comfortably making all in Stratford hunter chase (2m1f, good) in May but has become far too inconsistent to rely upon, and did not get competitive when reappearing in a recent Worcester handicap.

column4: Never Say Die IPA Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Mahons Glory, 7/2 Time To Bite, 4/1 Champagne Gold, 5/1 El Rio, 6/1 Coastguard Station, 8/1 Jet Plane, 20/1 Frere d'Armes
column36: Won at Ascot in March and has held his form fairly well since; probably won't be far away
column37: Returned from break with career-best performance at Ascot (2m1f, good) in March and has held his form fairly well since; should be okay over today's longer trip and is now back on that last winning mark; probably won't be far away.

column4: Never Say Die IPA Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 Mahons Glory, 7/2 Time To Bite, 4/1 Champagne Gold, 5/1 El Rio, 6/1 Coastguard Station, 8/1 Jet Plane, 20/1 Frere d'Armes
column36: Late-maturing 10yo who has won five good-ground chases this year; commands respect
column37: Late-maturing 10yo who has won five good-ground chases this year; easily made all at Newton Abbot (2m5f) on last two appearances and should be fine on this right-handed track; commands respect in current mood.

column37: Useful and versatile when trained in Ireland by Willie Mullins; absent since below-par run in Grade 3 novice chase in summer 2023 but reverts to hurdling on good mark for new stable; market helpful.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max

column37: Won over fences at Uttoxeter (2m, good) in June and ran well when back over hurdles there (2m4f, good) this month; remains on a workable mark and is 2-2 at this track; shortlisted.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column36: Career-best form when leading close home in valuable Summer Hurdle over C&D in July
column37: Posted career-best performance when leading close home in valuable Summer Hurdle over C&D (good) in July; 6lb higher today but confirmed his wellbeing with a good Flat run last month; probably won't be far away.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column36: Won first four hurdle races; close fourth over C&D in Summer Hurdle last time
column37: Launched hurdling career with four consecutive wins this spring/summer and maintained his progress with close fourth behind Cavern Club in Summer Hurdle over C&D (good) last time; remains of strong interest.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column36: Placed in Swinton at Haydock in May and again ran well in C&D Summer Hurdle; likely player
column37: 3-9 over hurdles; very creditable third in Swinton Hurdle at Haydock (1m7f, good) in May and again ran well when close fifth in C&D Summer Hurdle (good) in July, having been quite badly bumped by Sir Galahad at penultimate flight; recently placed on the Flat; likely contender.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column36: In excellent form over 2m4f in spring (three wins); drops back in trip after a break
column37: Made excellent progress towards end of last season, winning three consecutive 2m4f handicaps (good/good to soft); may still have significant further improvement to come but has fitness to prove after 160-day absence and is not sure to be suited by this drop back to 2m.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column36: Needs to better last couple of efforts but this C&D suits him very well
column37: Won small-field C&D event in June and was not beaten far in Summer Hurdle (a race he won in 2024) here in July; needs to up his game after two lesser efforts elsewhere but the return to this track is sure to suit.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column36: Dual Flat winner for new stable this spring before very good C&D third on hurdling return
column37: Dual Flat winner for new stable in the spring before reverting to hurdling with commendable third behind Cavern Club in C&D Summer Hurdle (good) in July; only 1lb higher today and ought to be right in the thick of things.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column36: Scored at Uttoxeter this month; 5lb rise might leave him vulnerable in this stronger race
column37: Seemingly aided by new tongue-tie since the summer, most notably when keeping on well to score at Uttoxeter (2m4f, good) 11 days ago; also suited by 2m but recent 5lb rise might leave him vulnerable in this competitive race.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column36: Dual winner at Worcester this season; may still be improving but this is a tough task
column37: Dual winner at Worcester (2m, good) this season and ran big race in defeat over that C&D three weeks ago; might still be on the upgrade but is another 4lb higher in this stronger contest.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max

column36: In good form on the Flat and over hurdles this year; not ruled out each-way
column37: Won at Cartmel (2m1f, soft) in June and stayed on for third off today's mark in competitive race there (good) last month; back hurdling after a recent Flat win and not ruled out each-way.

column4: Docks Beers Lincoln Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 5/1 Sir Galahad,  Goblet Of Fire, 6/1 Nibras Gold, 8/1 Cavern Club,  Busy Being Busy,  Ghasham, 12/1 Rock On Pedro, 14/1 Gale Mahler,  Oslo,  Scintillante,  Saligo Bay, 16/1 Castel Gandolfo, 20/1 Tax For Max
column27: A O'Brien,M Al Monsour& K Al' Attiyah

column37: Just 1-13 over hurdles but he did not have race run to suit his patient tactics when close second on recent stable debut at Worcester (2m4f, good to soft); moves up from Class 5 and competes from 4lb out of the weights but is dangerous to ignore nevertheless; sports first-time blinkers.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle

column37: 3-12 over hurdles, the latest win gained in small field at Huntingdon (2m3f, good) in May; only 2lb higher here but this summer's hurdle/Flat form was below-par.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle
column20: 3/1 Queens Wish, 7/2 Start Again, 9/2 Bannister, 8/1 Ikigai Star,  Gms Prince, 10/1 Soldat Forte,  Vivid Pink, 14/1 Little Soiree, 20/1 Lord Warburton, 33/1 Leading Lion

column36: Safely held when sixth over C&D last month but won a division of this race in 2024
column37: Unable to land a telling blow from off the pace when sixth over C&D six weeks ago but is now 2lb lower than when winning a division of this race on good ground a year ago; must be considered.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle
column20: 3/1 Queens Wish, 7/2 Start Again, 9/2 Bannister, 8/1 Ikigai Star,  Gms Prince, 10/1 Soldat Forte,  Vivid Pink, 14/1 Little Soiree, 20/1 Lord Warburton, 33/1 Leading Lion

column37: Scored at Huntingdon (2m, good) for Chris Gordon in May but left that stable after a disappointing run in June and was last of seven for new stable at Hexham (2m, good) last month; arrives here with a point to prove.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle
column20: 3/1 Queens Wish, 7/2 Start Again, 9/2 Bannister, 8/1 Ikigai Star,  Gms Prince, 10/1 Soldat Forte,  Vivid Pink, 14/1 Little Soiree, 20/1 Lord Warburton, 33/1 Leading Lion
column36: Pulled up in both chases this season and also disappointed when back over hurdles
column37: Pulled up in two chases this season, after a layoff, and soundly beaten when back over hurdles in first-time cheekpieces three weeks ago; very well handicapped on old form but current ability is hard to gauge.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle
column20: 3/1 Queens Wish, 7/2 Start Again, 9/2 Bannister, 8/1 Ikigai Star,  Gms Prince, 10/1 Soldat Forte,  Vivid Pink, 14/1 Little Soiree, 20/1 Lord Warburton, 33/1 Leading Lion
column36: Didn't get home after racing too freely on latest outing but still has low mileage
column37: Low-mileage mare who kept on for respectable third on stable debut at Stratford (2m, good) in June; didn't get home after racing too freely over 2m4f Uttoxeter this month but has possibilities if she settles better here.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle
column20: 3/1 Queens Wish, 7/2 Start Again, 9/2 Bannister, 8/1 Ikigai Star,  Gms Prince, 10/1 Soldat Forte,  Vivid Pink, 14/1 Little Soiree, 20/1 Lord Warburton, 33/1 Leading Lion
column36: In poor form over hurdles and on Flat this year; has lots to prove on stable debut
column37: Won over hurdles for Gordon Elliott in Ireland last summer but in poor form over hurdles and on the Flat for Tracy Leeson this year; makes debut for latest new stable with huge amount to prove; blinkers removed.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle
column20: 3/1 Queens Wish, 7/2 Start Again, 9/2 Bannister, 8/1 Ikigai Star,  Gms Prince, 10/1 Soldat Forte,  Vivid Pink, 14/1 Little Soiree, 20/1 Lord Warburton, 33/1 Leading Lion
column36: Good second at Huntingdon last October; absent since pulled up the following month
column37: 0-6 over hurdles; came second in Huntingdon handicap (2m3f, good) last October and has claims here if judged on that performance but we haven't seen her since a poor run the following month.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle
column20: 3/1 Queens Wish, 7/2 Start Again, 9/2 Bannister, 8/1 Ikigai Star,  Gms Prince, 10/1 Soldat Forte,  Vivid Pink, 14/1 Little Soiree, 20/1 Lord Warburton, 33/1 Leading Lion
column36: Ran quite well when placed two starts ago but is 0-20 over hurdles now; others preferred
column37: Ran well when third (albeit well held in the end) at Stratford (2m2f, good) in July and had excuse for subsequent poor performance (irregular heartbeat) but he's 0-20 over hurdles now; others preferred.

column4: Hard Graft Pale Ale Handicap Hurdle
column20: 3/1 Queens Wish, 7/2 Start Again, 9/2 Bannister, 8/1 Ikigai Star,  Gms Prince, 10/1 Soldat Forte,  Vivid Pink, 14/1 Little Soiree, 20/1 Lord Warburton, 33/1 Leading Lion
column36: Surprise winner of a division of this race in 2024 but generally very disappointing since
column37: Caused 33-1 surprise off today's mark in a division of this race a year ago (good ground) but generally very disappointing on the Flat/over hurdles since; headgear switched again today; too hard to predict.

column4: Tattersalls Online Royal Lodge Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)

column32: Michael Tabor & Derrick Smith & Mrs John Magnier
column36: His Galway form has taken some knocks but this scopey colt looks sure to progress
column37: Close relative of dual Derby winner Lambourn; the form of his Galway win (extended 1m, good to yielding) has taken some knocks but this Frankel colt is a sizeable unit and looks sure to progress with his racing; one of two runners for Aidan O'Brien who had seven entered at the five-day stage.

column4: Tattersalls Online Royal Lodge Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/4 Bow Echo, 4/1 Pacific Avenue, 5/1 Action,  Humidity, 11/2 Daytona, 15/2 Ancient Egypt, 100/1 Tailgunner Joe, 200/1 Lord Britain
column36: More workmanlike than flashy in winning his novices at Beverley and Goodwood
column37: 1,100,000gns Frankel colt; has been more workmanlike than flashy in winning his novices at Beverley and Goodwood (1m; both on good to firm) but there's no knocking an unbeaten start and he might be the type who only does enough in his races (reportedly a lazy worker at home); has to improve at this level but that's very feasible.

column4: Tattersalls Online Royal Lodge Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/4 Bow Echo, 4/1 Pacific Avenue, 5/1 Action,  Humidity, 11/2 Daytona, 15/2 Ancient Egypt, 100/1 Tailgunner Joe, 200/1 Lord Britain
column36: Impressed on debut and then floored a respected rival in a Listed race at Haydock
column37: Both runs over 1m on good ground; impressive when making light work of a subsequent winner at Newbury and was nicely on top at the finish when having to dig deeper to secure a Listed race at Haydock (runner-up well regarded in a top yard); reportedly thrilled his connections in a recent gallop.

column4: Tattersalls Online Royal Lodge Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/4 Bow Echo, 4/1 Pacific Avenue, 5/1 Action,  Humidity, 11/2 Daytona, 15/2 Ancient Egypt, 100/1 Tailgunner Joe, 200/1 Lord Britain
column36: Already smart before finishing third in a French Group 3 which didn't go to plan
column37: Looked good on his debut and confirmed that promise with an easy win at Listed level (Naas; 1m, good); relinquished his unbeaten record when odds-on for a Group 3 at Deauville but the drop back to 7f probably didn't help, nor being isolated from the two who beat him; big colt who retains significant potential for 1m+.

column4: Tattersalls Online Royal Lodge Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/4 Bow Echo, 4/1 Pacific Avenue, 5/1 Action,  Humidity, 11/2 Daytona, 15/2 Ancient Egypt, 100/1 Tailgunner Joe, 200/1 Lord Britain
column36: Leads the way on Topspeed/RPR figures and promises to be even better at 1m
column37: The Chesham winner (good to firm) who didn't look at home on the undulations of Goodwood when beaten for the first time in a strong edition of the Group 2 Vintage Stakes; got himself firmly back on track when perhaps unfortunate not to have won Sandown's Group 3 Solario Stakes having been bumped quite severely late on; leads the way on Topspeed/RPR figures and promises to be even better at 1m.

column4: Tattersalls Online Royal Lodge Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/4 Bow Echo, 4/1 Pacific Avenue, 5/1 Action,  Humidity, 11/2 Daytona, 15/2 Ancient Egypt, 100/1 Tailgunner Joe, 200/1 Lord Britain
column36: Came up short under a penalty in latest novice and has no right to be winning this
column37: All runs over 7f on the AW; the horse he beat at Kempton has since waltzed home in a nursery but this colt then came up short under a penalty and has no right to be troubling the best of these.

column4: Tattersalls Online Royal Lodge Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/4 Bow Echo, 4/1 Pacific Avenue, 5/1 Action,  Humidity, 11/2 Daytona, 15/2 Ancient Egypt, 100/1 Tailgunner Joe, 200/1 Lord Britain
column36: Big run in the Solario for one so inexperienced and this drier ground can benefit
column37: 9-1 when surprising an odds-on stablemate (since placed at Group 2 and Grade 1 level) on the July course (good to firm) and was conceding experience to Humidity when hot on the heels of that rival in the Group 3 Solario at Sandown; threatened to win that day until passed late on and this drier ground could benefit, as should the step up from 7f; much respected.

column4: Tattersalls Online Royal Lodge Stakes (Group 2) (Colts & Geldings)
column20: 7/4 Bow Echo, 4/1 Pacific Avenue, 5/1 Action,  Humidity, 11/2 Daytona, 15/2 Ancient Egypt, 100/1 Tailgunner Joe, 200/1 Lord Britain
column36: Won his maiden at Catterick and finished last behind Bow Echo at Haydock when a 50-1 shot
column37: Won his maiden at Catterick (7f, soft) and finished last behind Bow Echo at Haydock when a 50-1 chance.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column36: Fine second to Royal Fixation in Lowther; well worth her place in this even higher grade
column37: 180,000euros breeze-up buy who hammered nine rivals by 12l and more on her debut at Haydock (6f, good) in July and found only Royal Fixation too strong when upped in class for the Group 2 Lowther at York (6f, good to firm) the following month; remains open to improvement and looks well worth her place in this even higher grade.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column32: Middleham Park Racing Lxiv Mrs L Millman
column36: Splendidly tough; won Super Sprint and a Salisbury Group 3; another personal best needed
column37: Splendidly tough type who won the Super Sprint (5f, good) in the summer and took her form to a new level when gamely landing the Group 3 Dick Poole at Salisbury (6f, soft) two weeks ago; keeps finding more but this assignment demands another personal best, and by some way.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column32: Derrick Smith & Mrs John Magnier & Michael Tabor
column36: Rapid progress in three runs; fine second in Curragh Group 1 last time; leading player
column37: Rapid progress in three runs; defeated odds-on Lady Iman in 6f Group 2 at the Curragh in June and was seen off only inside the final 1f in the Group 1 Moyglare Stud there (7f, yielding) 13 days ago; may not have reached her ceiling just yet; one of two strong contenders for the Aidan O'Brien yard.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column36: Followed win in Ascot Group 3 with good second in French Group 2; this is harder still
column37: Assembling an impressive CV and followed a win in the 6f Group 3 Princess Margaret Stakes at Ascot with a good second in the 7f Group 2 Prix du Calvados at Deauville; handles quick ground and likely to give her running again but this is her stiffest task so far.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column36: Won first two races and had an excuse last time; lots to find but may still be unexposed
column37: Made a promising start with wins at Beverley (5f, good to firm) and York (6f, good) in July, and she probably raced on the wrong part of the track when only seventh to Anthelia and Orion's Belt in a Group 3 at Salisbury; plenty to find on form but she may still have untapped potential.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column36: Close second in French Group 3; improvement required to come out on top in first Group 1
column37: Hard to knock after a win in a Listed race at Naas and a close second in a Group 3 at Longchamp (both 5f on ground softer than good), but her form might have plateaued and she'll need some improvement to come out on top in her first Group 1.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column36: Beaten only by Anthelia in Salisbury Group 3 last time; faces a stern assignment on form
column37: Won on the July course in the summer and seemed suited by the drop back in distance when beaten only by Anthelia in Salisbury Group 3 (6f, soft; also handles good to firm) two weeks ago; should run her race but faces a stern assignment on form.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column36: Looked a high-class juvenile when quickening well to win the Lowther; the one to beat
column37: All three runs at 6f on good to firm; went close in the Group 2 Duchess of Cambridge on the July course and she looked a high-class juvenile when quickening well to beat America Queen by 1l in the Group 2 Lowther at York last month; seems highly regarded and could be anything; probably the one to beat.

column4: Tattersalls Sceptre Sessions Cheveley Park Stakes (Group 1) (Fillies)
column20: 13/8 Royal Fixation, 7/2 Beautify, 4/1 True Love, 9/2 America Queen, 14/1 Fitzella, 16/1 Anthelia, 20/1 Havana Anna, 33/1 Orion's Belt, 66/1 Golden Palace
column32: Michael Tabor & Derrick Smith & Mrs John Magnier
column36: Promising winner of two Group 2s and had excuse for Group 1 defeat last time; dangerous
column37: Showed mild lameness afterwards when beaten at 1-4 in the Group 1 Phoenix Stakes at the Curragh seven weeks ago; had previously looked very promising indeed, winning Group 2s at Royal Ascot (beat 22 rivals in Queen Mary) and the Curragh (cruised home in Railway) in the summer; commands major respect as she bids to redeem her reputation.

column37: Beat stablemate Kansas in Curragh maiden then ran well on the figures in the Group 2 July Stakes (6f, good to firm); beaten favourite, showing no further progress, in Listed and sales races since; fitting of tongue-tie needs to have a boosting effect.

column20: 11/10 Wise Approach, 9/2 The Publican's Son, 7/1 Coppull, 8/1 Hilitany, 10/1 Kansas, 12/1 Five Ways, 16/1 Brussels,  Havana Hurricane, 66/1 First Approach
column36: Progressive form on home soil features Group 2 Richmond Stakes win; remains of interest
column37: Took a step backwards (behind Wise Approach) in the Prix Morny last time but has progressive form on home soil and may well rebound; placed in the Coventry at Royal Ascot then comfortably landed the Richmond Stakes at Goodwood (6f, good; Group 2); remains of interest.

column20: 11/10 Wise Approach, 9/2 The Publican's Son, 7/1 Coppull, 8/1 Hilitany, 10/1 Kansas, 12/1 Five Ways, 16/1 Brussels,  Havana Hurricane, 66/1 First Approach
column32: Mrs John Magnier & Michael Tabor & Derrick Smith
column36: Bottom of this pack on bare figures and is an exposed sort
column37: One of three Ballydoyle runners; produced peak effort in Listed grade; bottom of this pack on the figures and record of just 1-8 reflects that he's an exposed sort now.

column20: 11/10 Wise Approach, 9/2 The Publican's Son, 7/1 Coppull, 8/1 Hilitany, 10/1 Kansas, 12/1 Five Ways, 16/1 Brussels,  Havana Hurricane, 66/1 First Approach

column37: Substandard winner of the Sirenia Stakes at Kempton (6f, AW; Group 3) where he made all and held on by only a neck, taking form figures to 411; however, he's an improving sort and plausibly hasn't reached his ceiling yet; gained his turf success on good to firm.

column20: 11/10 Wise Approach, 9/2 The Publican's Son, 7/1 Coppull, 8/1 Hilitany, 10/1 Kansas, 12/1 Five Ways, 16/1 Brussels,  Havana Hurricane, 66/1 First Approach
column36: Solid operator; should give his running but has seemingly reached his ceiling
column37: Windsor Castle winner who has proved a solid operator and ran creditably in the Flying Childers (5f, good; Group 2) at Doncaster most recently, taking record to 121234; very likely to give his running but has seemingly reached his ceiling (form has levelled off).

column20: 11/10 Wise Approach, 9/2 The Publican's Son, 7/1 Coppull, 8/1 Hilitany, 10/1 Kansas, 12/1 Five Ways, 16/1 Brussels,  Havana Hurricane, 66/1 First Approach
column36: Impressively defied a penalty in latest novice start and looks potentially smart
column37: £300,000 breeze-up purchase; impressively defied a penalty in latest novice start, completing a Windsor double (6f, good/good to firm); won those two races by an aggregate of about 9l and looks potentially smart; interesting contender upped in class.

column20: 11/10 Wise Approach, 9/2 The Publican's Son, 7/1 Coppull, 8/1 Hilitany, 10/1 Kansas, 12/1 Five Ways, 16/1 Brussels,  Havana Hurricane, 66/1 First Approach
column32: M Tabor & D Smith & Mrs J Magnier & Westerberg
column36: Very consistent; ran well in the Flying Childers but needs additional progress
column37: Ballydoyle colt who has proved very consistent and ran well in the Flying Childers at Doncaster (5f, good; Group 2) most recently, taking record to 3231222; needs additional progress to land this prize and was beaten by stablemate Brussels in sole 6f attempt.

column20: 11/10 Wise Approach, 9/2 The Publican's Son, 7/1 Coppull, 8/1 Hilitany, 10/1 Kansas, 12/1 Five Ways, 16/1 Brussels,  Havana Hurricane, 66/1 First Approach
column36: Strong-finishing second in Curragh Group 3 on debut; open to any amount of progress
column37: $20,000 yearling, $200,000 (breeze-up) 2yo; has a US pedigree; belied his 40-1 odds with strong-finishing second in Group 3 contest at the Curragh (6f, good to yielding) where he was the sole newcomer in a field of ten; could go one better, being open to any amount of progress.

column20: 11/10 Wise Approach, 9/2 The Publican's Son, 7/1 Coppull, 8/1 Hilitany, 10/1 Kansas, 12/1 Five Ways, 16/1 Brussels,  Havana Hurricane, 66/1 First Approach
column36: Close third in the Morny; top on ratings and is half-brother to a Middle Park winner
column37: Cost 1,000,000 guineas as a yearling and has developed into a smart colt, with ready Listed win at Newbury flanked by good efforts at Royal Ascot and Deauville, close third in the Prix Morny (6f, good) last time; top on ratings and aptly bred, being half-brother to a Middle Park winner.

column20: 9/2 Treble Tee, 6/1 Fifth Column, 8/1 Westridge, 9/1 Fort George, 11/1 Tribal Chief, 12/1 Real Gain,  Greek Order, 14/1 Boiling Point, 16/1 Thunder Run,  Treasure Time, 20/1 Ebt's Guard,  Cash,  Great Chieftain,  Mister Winston, 25/1 Marhaba Ghaiyyath,  Erzindjan,  Urban Lion,  Mr Swivell,  Indalo, 33/1 Dutch Decoy,  Sir Paul Ramsey, 40/1 Savvy Victory, 50/1 Silver Sword,  Divine Knight

column20: 9/2 Treble Tee, 6/1 Fifth Column, 8/1 Westridge, 9/1 Fort George, 11/1 Tribal Chief, 12/1 Real Gain,  Greek Order, 14/1 Boiling Point, 16/1 Thunder Run,  Treasure Time, 20/1 Ebt's Guard,  Cash,  Great Chieftain,  Mister Winston, 25/1 Marhaba Ghaiyyath,  Erzindjan,  Urban Lion,  Mr Swivell,  Indalo, 33/1 Dutch Decoy,  Sir Paul Ramsey, 40/1 Savvy Victory, 50/1 Silver Sword,  Divine Knight

column20: 9/2 Treble Tee, 6/1 Fifth Column, 8/1 Westridge, 9/1 Fort George, 11/1 Tribal Chief, 12/1 Real Gain,  Greek Order, 14/1 Boiling Point, 16/1 Thunder Run,  Treasure Time, 20/1 Ebt's Guard,  Cash,  Great Chieftain,  Mister Winston, 25/1 Marhaba Ghaiyyath,  Erzindjan,  Urban Lion,  Mr Swivell,  Indalo, 33/1 Dutch Decoy,  Sir Paul Ramsey, 40/1 Savvy Victory, 50/1 Silver Sword,  Divine Knight

column20: 9/2 Treble Tee, 6/1 Fifth Column, 8/1 Westridge, 9/1 Fort George, 11/1 Tribal Chief, 12/1 Real Gain,  Greek Order, 14/1 Boiling Point, 16/1 Thunder Run,  Treasure Time, 20/1 Ebt's Guard,  Cash,  Great Chieftain,  Mister Winston, 25/1 Marhaba Ghaiyyath,  Erzindjan,  Urban Lion,  Mr Swivell,  Indalo, 33/1 Dutch Decoy,  Sir Paul Ramsey, 40/1 Savvy Victory, 50/1 Silver Sword,  Divine Knight

column20: 9/2 Treble Tee, 6/1 Fifth Column, 8/1 Westridge, 9/1 Fort George, 11/1 Tribal Chief, 12/1 Real Gain,  Greek Order, 14/1 Boiling Point, 16/1 Thunder Run,  Treasure Time, 20/1 Ebt's Guard,  Cash,  Great Chieftain,  Mister Winston, 25/1 Marhaba Ghaiyyath,  Erzindjan,  Urban Lion,  Mr Swivell,  Indalo, 33/1 Dutch Decoy,  Sir Paul Ramsey, 40/1 Savvy Victory, 50/1 Silver Sword,  Divine Knight

column37: Won two in a row in May (1m, good; including here); merely midfield at Goodwood 34 days ago but that was his first run for three months and he may have needed it; not discounted in view of previous, progressive form.

column37: Won in a big field at York (1m, good to firm) last August and he's unexposed at today's trip, which could suit; best run of this light campaign came when fourth at Ascot last month but he needs something extra today.

column20: 7/2 Assaranca, 4/1 Conjecture,  Zooter, 9/2 Bearin Up, 5/1 Renovatio Angel, 7/1 Supreme Clarets, 14/1 Fairydale

column20: 7/2 Gold Star Hero, 5/1 Vince L'Amour, 11/2 Smart Vision, 10/1 Mission Command,  High Opinion,  Miss Brazen, 12/1 Illusionist,  Wen Moon,  Mark's Choice, 14/1 Albegone,  Copper Knight, 16/1 Cayman Tai, 20/1 Glory Fighter

column20: 7/2 Gold Star Hero, 5/1 Vince L'Amour, 11/2 Smart Vision, 10/1 Mission Command,  High Opinion,  Miss Brazen, 12/1 Illusionist,  Wen Moon,  Mark's Choice, 14/1 Albegone,  Copper Knight, 16/1 Cayman Tai, 20/1 Glory Fighter

column20: 7/2 Gold Star Hero, 5/1 Vince L'Amour, 11/2 Smart Vision, 10/1 Mission Command,  High Opinion,  Miss Brazen, 12/1 Illusionist,  Wen Moon,  Mark's Choice, 14/1 Albegone,  Copper Knight, 16/1 Cayman Tai, 20/1 Glory Fighter

column20: 7/2 Gold Star Hero, 5/1 Vince L'Amour, 11/2 Smart Vision, 10/1 Mission Command,  High Opinion,  Miss Brazen, 12/1 Illusionist,  Wen Moon,  Mark's Choice, 14/1 Albegone,  Copper Knight, 16/1 Cayman Tai, 20/1 Glory Fighter

column20: 7/2 Gold Star Hero, 5/1 Vince L'Amour, 11/2 Smart Vision, 10/1 Mission Command,  High Opinion,  Miss Brazen, 12/1 Illusionist,  Wen Moon,  Mark's Choice, 14/1 Albegone,  Copper Knight, 16/1 Cayman Tai, 20/1 Glory Fighter

column20: 7/2 Gold Star Hero, 5/1 Vince L'Amour, 11/2 Smart Vision, 10/1 Mission Command,  High Opinion,  Miss Brazen, 12/1 Illusionist,  Wen Moon,  Mark's Choice, 14/1 Albegone,  Copper Knight, 16/1 Cayman Tai, 20/1 Glory Fighter

column20: 7/2 Gold Star Hero, 5/1 Vince L'Amour, 11/2 Smart Vision, 10/1 Mission Command,  High Opinion,  Miss Brazen, 12/1 Illusionist,  Wen Moon,  Mark's Choice, 14/1 Albegone,  Copper Knight, 16/1 Cayman Tai, 20/1 Glory Fighter

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap
column20: 100/30 Another Baar, 4/1 Eye Of Dubai, 8/1 Strong Warrior,  Beaujolais Nouveau,  Station X, 10/1 Korker,  Mister Sox, 12/1 Aleezdancer, 14/1 Sophia's Starlight, 16/1 Fortamour, 20/1 Intervention,  Manila Scouse

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap
column20: 100/30 Another Baar, 4/1 Eye Of Dubai, 8/1 Strong Warrior,  Beaujolais Nouveau,  Station X, 10/1 Korker,  Mister Sox, 12/1 Aleezdancer, 14/1 Sophia's Starlight, 16/1 Fortamour, 20/1 Intervention,  Manila Scouse

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column37: C&D winner; responded well to a change of tactics when making all at Pontefract in July (6f, good); not so good in either start since but not handicapped out of things if bouncing back.

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column37: Better known for his AW exploits but he enjoyed a big win on turf when making all up the far rail to win the Great St Wilfrid over C&D last month (good to firm); two lesser efforts have followed; opposable.

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column4: Ripon Cathedral City Of The Dales Handicap

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star

column37: Ten-race maiden but he's shaped well on a few occasions; returning to 6f looks in his favour and his lacklustre run here last year came on heavy ground; a possible.

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star
column36: 2-4 since tried in blinkers, the wins coming over 6f at Catterick; has course form; chance

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star

column36: Chasing a hat-trick after two narrow wins in July; contender despite her 4lb higher mark

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star
column36: Best run this year came at Southwell this month; not certain to back it up

column20: 9/2 Annie Edson Taylor, 7/1 Big Apple Jack,  Mrs Trump, 9/1 Fenlander,  Dream Deal, 10/1 Flowstate,  Roundhay Park,  Back Before Dark,  Hurstwood, 12/1 Mattice,  Eldeyaar, 14/1 Barmyblade, 16/1 Ifonlytheycudtalk, 33/1 Ziva's Star

column4: Thank You To Our Groundstaff Novice Stakes (GBB Race)

column4: Thank You To Our Groundstaff Novice Stakes (GBB Race)
